	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> " He was one of the most notable Syriac prose writers and a vehement champion of Miaphysitism. In\n               Ethiopia he is known above all as an author of a monastic treaty Filkǝsyos, which\n             however is a misattribution. In fact, what might be actual translations of his works into Gǝʿǝz are\n           very rare but cf. eg. EMML 1763, f. 129r-132v." .
